14. Create Deny-All Network Policy
Now we start security.
Switch project:
oc project network-policy
________________________________________
Edit file:
deny-all.yaml
Policy:
kind: NetworkPolicy
apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1
metadata:
  name: deny-all
spec:
  podSelector: {}
________________________________________
Explanation
Field	Meaning
podSelector {}	select ALL pods
no ingress rules	deny incoming traffic
Effect:
Block all incoming traffic
________________________________________
Create policy:
oc create -f deny-all.yaml
Check:
oc get networkpolicy
Output:
deny-all
________________________________________
15. Verify Traffic is Blocked
Test:
oc rsh test-pod curl hello-pod
Result:
No response
Meaning:
Traffic blocked
________________________________________
Test cross namespace:
oc rsh sample-app curl test-pod
Result:
Timeout
Meaning:
network-policy working
________________________________________
16. Create Allow-Specific Policy
Goal:
Allow:
sample-app → hello pod
Only:
port 8080
________________________________________
File:
allow-specific.yaml
Policy:
spec:
  podSelector:
    matchLabels:
      deployment: hello
  ingress:
  - from:
    - namespaceSelector:
        matchLabels:
          network: different-namespace
      podSelector:
        matchLabels:
          deployment: sample-app
    ports:
    - port: 8080
      protocol: TCP
________________________________________
17. Policy Explanation
Select Target Pods
podSelector
deployment: hello
Meaning:
Policy applies only to hello pods
________________________________________
Define Allowed Source
from:
________________________________________
Namespace Selector
namespaceSelector:
  matchLabels:
    network: different-namespace
Meaning:
allow traffic from namespace
________________________________________
Pod Selector
deployment: sample-app
Meaning:
only sample-app pod
________________________________________
Port Restriction
ports:
- port: 8080
Meaning:
only port 8080 allowed
________________________________________
18. Apply the Policy
Command:
oc create -n network-policy -f allow-specific.yaml
Check policies:
oc get networkpolicies
Example:
deny-all
allow-specific
